  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_1' aria-label=\" The State of Haryana versus Jai Singh and Others pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('1','2025','2025_9_1016_1052','2025INSC1122'); ><font size='4'> <strong>THE STATE OF HARYANA<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>JAI SINGH AND OTHERS </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 9 S.C.R. 1016</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 1122</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010008752025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : BHUSHAN RAMKRISHNA GAVAI<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, PRASHANT KUMAR MISHRA, K.V. VISWANATHAN</strong><br> Issue for Consideration The issue pertains to assail the correctness of the Judgment and Order passed by the Full Bench of High Court wherein the writ petition preferred by the proprietors/landowners, (Respondents herein), challenging the amendments carried out in the Punjab Act, 1961, as inserted by the Haryana Act No. 9 of 1992 was partly allowed. Headnotes&dagger; Punjab Village Common Lands (Regulation) Act, 1961 &ndash; sub-clause (6) to s.2(g) &ndash; East Punjab Holdings (Consolidation And Prevention of Fragmentation) Act, 1948 &ndash; Constitution<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 16-09-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 6990/2014</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Dismissed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 3 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('1','2025','2025_9_1016_1052','2025INSC1122','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-